description:
Single-banded subspecies of the Three-banded Ladybird Beetle (Coccinella trifasciata subversa), photographed on some Poison Hemlock (Conium maculatum) along Coyote Creek in Milpitas, CA.  Location was at the Coyote Creek Trailhead near the maintenance facility at the north end of McCarthy Ranch Boulevard.  Apparently, subversa is the dominant form of C. trifasciata in the San Francisco Bay Area.  The nominate form usually has three black bands on its abdomen.
